Interface DsaTree<ElemType>

Type Parameters:
ElemType - the type of elements held in this tree. The elements must support comparison for equality, either by:
  • Providing a meaningful result from Object.equals(Object) implementation, or
  • Using a custom Comparator provided by the user.
All Known Subinterfaces:
DsaBST<ElemType>, DsaHeap<ElemType>
All Known Implementing Classes:
DsaBinarySearchTree, DsaMaxHeap, DsaMinHeap
public interface DsaTree<ElemType>
A generic interface for implementing a tree data structure.

  • Method Details

    • size

      int size()
      Returns the number of elements in the tree. It is guaranteed that size() == 0 if and only if isEmpty() returns true.
      Returns:
      the size of the tree

    • insert

      void insert(ElemType value)
      Inserts the specified value into the tree.
      Parameters:
      value - the value to insert
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if value is null

    • isEmpty

      boolean isEmpty()
      Checks whether the tree is empty. A tree is considered empty if it has no elements. It is guaranteed that isEmpty() returns true if and only if size() == 0.
      Returns:
      true if the tree contains no elements, false otherwise
